H0.text: The nictitating membrane is found on which part of animal’s body. Nose

H1.text: The nictitating membrane is found on which part of animal’s body. Ear

H2.text: The nictitating membrane is found on which part of animal’s body. Mouth

H3.text: The nictitating membrane is found on which part of animal’s body. Eye

A4.text: The nictitating membrane is a transparent or translucent third eyelid present in some animals that can be drawn across the eye from the medial canthus to protect and moisten it while maintaining vision.
